    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1: In a neuronal culture model of LTP, activation of NMDARs by bath application of the coagonist glycine causes an increase in the surface expression of endogenous GluA1-containing AMPARs compared to untreated control cells. ShRNA-mediated Stx-3 KD significantly impaired both glycine-induced increases in GluA1 surface expression in culture and LTP recorded in acute slices.\nFigure 2: mEPSC amplitude nor its frequency were affected by the Stx-3 KD. Thus, postsynaptic Stx-3 is not required for basal transmission.. Experimental description: M&M:CD1 (Charles River) mice (8-12 g) were prepared for stereotactic injection of lentiviruses using standard procedures.",
